data.title: What's for dinner?  Jimmychangas!!
data.text: This is always a win when we are undecided for dinner. The tacos are on home tortillas, which I found out today can be cooked more well done. The green salsa is amazing. The only issue is the parking. There is parking across the street, which cost about five dollars for two hours.

data.title: Food is good but over priced and staff is slow
data.text: It's a good place to get a solid burrito or tacos. But for Mexican it should be this expensive. Also, it took a long time for fairly simple tacos. I will go back but only because there isn't better Mexican within this area.

data.title: Great tacos and such!
data.text:
I've been here before but took my hubby for a quick lunch.  Man, was it good!  I had a steak taco and a carnitas taco and he had a Jimmychanga.  The tacos are soooo good (I get all the stuff on it) and the Jimmychanga was huge and delicious.  

There's not much space for sitting - a few 2-person tables outside, a couple of 2-person hi-tops and counter seating inside.

data.title: Really good tacos!
data.text: Wish I could say more about this place but I only had a few tacos here the other day and I have to say they were awesome! Two steak tacos stuffed with meat - really very good stuff. Can't wait to go back and try a burrito or quesadilla, but I'm sure they are just as good. Be forewarned - there is NO parking nearby other than the parking garage just down the street. Also, at first appearance you may be turned off by the size of the place. It is small and there is seating inside as well as outside, but don't be deterred! The tacos are excellent!! Service was friendly, informative and quick. I'll be back - hope I can edit this review so I can add comments on other food items!

data.title: Best mexican food ever
data.text: Jimmy, Alberto ans their team are great. The food is tasty and the meals are huuuuuge. I recommand 1000 times.

data.title: A Mexican Restaurant That Is Earning Customers Everyday
data.text:
I discovered this modest restaurant, Jimmychangas thanks to my daughter.  We order regularly and often have it delivered promptly.

The food is fresh, affordable and traditional.  Few Mexican restaurants are respected by the culinary crowd in West Palm Beach.  We will likely order today for "Cinco de Mayo".  My tastebuds are dancing at the mere thought of a meal from Jimmychangas.

I urge everyone to give this gem a try!

data.title: Tasty Tacos!
data.text: We recently found a flyer for Jimmychangas on our gate. Today, we decided to give them a try. The chicken tacos with the extras were very good! The cilantro wasn't covered up, even with the extras. It's only a few minutes from our house, so I expect that we'll be back.

data.title: AMAZING
data.text: I went to this hidden gem thanks to a Facebook posting. I ordered the grilled chicken chimichanga and my sister had the carnitas burrito. I can't decide which of the two was bursting more with flavor. It was fresh and delicious. The service was excellent on the phone and upon arrival to pick up. We cannot wait to be back and try everything else! I highly recommend this place.

data.title: Jury Duty Lunch
data.text:
Found this place looking for a close lunch spot near the courthouse. They have a very small eat in area and a few chairs/tables outside. Weather was beautiful so I sat outside. 
I had the taco special (2 tacos, chips & salsa, slaw and a coke) for under $10.  
Flavors were very good. Tacos were small but delicious. Slaw was excellent - very unique. Chips were homemade but a little too much salt. 
Service was prompt and friendly. 
I'll be back.

data.title: Small portions. Big prices.
data.text: The food was not very flavorful or made well. The portions were small. I am all for local, but I do not want to even try again.

data.title: Lots of food
data.text: We did take out on this trip. The girl behind the counter was super friendly. We ordered a burrito, chimichanga, and chips with guac. It was an incredible amount of food for a very inexpensive price. We were very pleased and the food was very good. We will definitely be back!

data.title: Great Mexican - take out and delivery
data.text: We ate in.  They only have seating for about 8 people.  The chips are home made and the salsa is wonderful.  Not the typical out of a jar served at most restaurants.  A friend and I split the Jimmychanga.  It had everything on it including cream cheese, sour cream, and guac.  Another friend had the steak chimichanga.  They gave us samples of their cabbage salad (no mayo or vinegar - just lemon juice and spices).  Everything was wonderful.  We'll definitely be back.

data.title: хорошее заведение  советую всем приходить
data.text: Обслуживание было превосходным по телефону и по прибытии в услугой трансфера. Мы не можем дождаться, чтобы вернуться и попробовать все остальное!...
